    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1b: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for Cbl-b and PSD-95 (DLG4) in cultured spinal cord dorsal horn neurons showed partial co-localization. Imaging resolution was too low to pinpoint precise synaptic localization.\n\nFigure 2: Cbl-b specifically interacts with NMDAR subunit GluN2B (GRIN2B) in co-immunoprecipitations from spinal cord dorsal horn of adult mice and HEK293T cells.\n\nFigure 3: Cbl-b enhanced the ubiquitination and reduced the surface expression of GluN2B in spinal neuron cultures and HEK293T cells.\n\nFigure 4: Cbl-b promotes the developmental decline of synaptic GluN2B receptors.. Experimental description: M&M: \"The primary neurons were cultured as described previously (26). Briefly, the mouse pups (P1) were decapitated, and the dorsal quadrants of spinal cords were dissected into ice-cold Hanks' balanced salt solution (HBSS) supplemented with 10 mM Hepes.\"\n\nantibody:\nrabbit anti-Cbl-b antibody (Proteintech, Rosemont, IL, USA)",
